reviews.text:
I was fortunate enough to have a sample sent to me by a friend with the cap SS at 0.25% I sat on this for about 10ml and it didnt really stand out to me. After a bit of a steep (and running out of juice on hand) I kept nipping at this until there was some aha moment where i just looked over at the bottle to assess (in fear) just how much of this I had left. This is the most telling sign of how good a mix is to me: How strong is the separation anxiety near the end? As for taste, I tried this blind only knowing it as Cornbread pudding. I swear I thought this was a butterscotch vape, tasting it. But better. BS can leave a cloying sweet trail that lingers in my throat long after it should have been gone, but that's the vibe here I get. Mid-inhale (im guessing, literally) that maple/corn/custard mix packs a warm smooth rich golden sweet with good body that doesnt come across as bakery, just a very nice mouthfeel, into something i can only describe as it's soft and warm and cozy. perfectly sweet, distinctive and yet familiar.&#xD;
&#xD;
this is a 5/5 mix, perfect also for fall time. if you are curious at all, dont hesitate to try this. well done!

great clone, gotta give credit where credit is due. Saved mixer as I believe this took some time.  Second 60ml batch just mixed. Subbed Cap VCV1 and tfa maple syrup but have FA maple coming in this week and will mix up another batch. &#xD;
